Key Match Events: Al Horford sank a pair of late triples off of dishes from Jayson Tatum, including one with less than two minutes remaining.
Horford drove past Chris Boucher for a vintage and-one floater over Ochai Agbaji with just over five minutes left in the game.
Post-Match Reflections: Horford made a play when it was time to make a play, according to head coach Joe Mazzulla.
The veteran's readiness and execution were crucial in the game's outcome.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Boston had six players score in double figures.
Jayson Tatum hit a game-winning shot in overtime.
